#Text=The Denver Nuggets ( 27 - 38 ) defeated the Phoenix Suns ( 17 - 48 ) 116 - 98 on Thursday .
#Text=The Nuggets were a rare nine - point favorite in this matchup and didn’t disappoint home fans .
#Text=They dominated every quarter except the third , as they outscored the Suns by at least seven points in the first , second and fourth quarters .
#Text=The three - point shooting was key for Denver , as they went 13 - for - 29 , with the Suns going just 6 - for - 28 .
#Text=The ball movement was huge as well , with the Nuggets handing out 27 assists to the Suns 19 .
#Text=The two big name rookie in this game didn’t disappoint , as Emmanuel Mudiay and Devin Booker both scored career - highs .
#Text=It 's been a rough stretch for the Suns , but there were some bright spots in this loss .
#Text=The most notable being that of Devin Booker , as he scored a career - high 35 points in a spectacular performance .
#Text=No other starter scored in double figures , with the other four players combing for 21 points .
#Text=Brandon Knight made his return in well over a month , as he scored 10 points off the bench .
#Text=Jon Leuer was the only other player in double figures , as he scored 19 points while grabbing seven boards of his own .
#Text=It doesn’t get much easier for Phoenix , as they travel to play the Golden State Warriors on Saturday in their next game .
#Text=The Nuggets played one of their best games of the season here to win their fourth game in their last five .
#Text=Rookie Emmanuel Mudiay was fantastic , as he scored a career - high 30 points , while also handing out five assists .
#Text=The other rookie starter played well too , as Nikola Jokic accumulated 18 points , 10 rebounds , four assists , two steals and three blocks in the win .
#Text=The bench also played well , as they combined for 52 points , 26 rebounds and 14 assists between six players .
#Text=Denver will look to keep up the recent good form against the Washington Wizards on Saturday .
